# =============================================================================
# Paytm Payment Gateway — environment variables
# =============================================================================
# Defaults below are pre-filled for STAGING. To go live:
#   1. Set PAYTM_ENVIRONMENT="production"
#   2. Replace PAYTM_MID / PAYTM_MERCHANT_KEY / PAYTM_WEBSITE_NAME with your
#      production credentials (staging keys do NOT work in production).
# =============================================================================

PAYTM_ENVIRONMENT="staging"
PAYTM_MID=""
PAYTM_MERCHANT_KEY=""
PAYTM_WEBSITE_NAME="WEBSTAGING"
PAYTM_CALLBACK_BASE="http://localhost:3001"

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional overrides — leave commented unless you need them
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PAYTM_PG_DOMAIN=""             # auto-derived from PAYTM_ENVIRONMENT
# PAYTM_CALLBACK_URL=""          # auto-derived from PAYTM_CALLBACK_BASE
# PAYTM_STATUS_API_URL=""        # auto-derived from PAYTM_PG_DOMAIN
# NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS="./certs/zscaler.crt"   # corp networks (Zscaler/Netskope) only

# =============================================================================
# How to get your MID and Merchant Key
# =============================================================================
# Both staging and production credentials are issued from the Paytm dashboard:
#   https://dashboard.paytmpayments.com/next/apikeys
#
# Staging (sandbox / test data):
#   1. Open the link above and sign in.
#   2. You land on the "Test API Details" tab by default.
#   3. Click "Generate Now" — staging MID and Merchant Key appear instantly.
#   4. Copy both into PAYTM_MID and PAYTM_MERCHANT_KEY above.
#
# Production (live payments):
#   1. Same URL, switch to the "Production API Details" tab.
#   2. Production keys are issued only after KYC + account activation.
#      If the tab shows nothing, finish onboarding or contact your Paytm KAM.
#   3. Copy MID and Merchant Key into the production block above.
#
# Always wrap the Merchant Key in double quotes — it can contain '#', '@', '$',
# which an unquoted .env value would treat as a comment / shell metacharacter.
#
# =============================================================================
# Field descriptions
# =============================================================================
# PAYTM_ENVIRONMENT  - "staging" (test) or "production" (live).
# PAYTM_MID          - Your unique Merchant ID provided by Paytm.
# PAYTM_MERCHANT_KEY - Secret key for checksum generation. Never expose publicly.
# PAYTM_WEBSITE_NAME - Per-MID identifier. Use "WEBSTAGING" for staging,
#                      the value Paytm provisioned (often "DEFAULT") for prod.
# PAYTM_CALLBACK_BASE - Public base URL where Paytm posts payment results.
#                       Must be reachable from the user's browser.
#
# =============================================================================
# Important notes
# =============================================================================
# - Use staging environment for testing integrations.
# - Switch to production only after successful staging tests.
# - Ensure callback URL is publicly reachable in production.
# - Never commit a filled-in .env or expose Merchant Key in client code.
